141-154 Prayers that the Getae may be subdued, and that all the world may contribute to the support of Rome and to her greatness.

141 sacrilegae hostia gentis, lit. ‘ victim consisting in the impious race,’ i.e. let the race itself, guilty of the sacrilege of taking Rome, fall as a victim; which means, not necessarily that all the Getae should be elain, but rather that. they should be conquered and subdued to Rome, as is, in fact, stated in the next line.
